  <text>
      <body>
         <p>Isis to RC. I will thank you my dear Richard, to send my cloak, and my clay [? clogs?] and to send me word, what time will be most convenient for me to see you to day. I am wear, and tired this morning and i want to coax you to nurse me a very little bit, as our friend has promised to come direct to the Compter, at the most convenient part of the afternoon, to herself[?], and i to come when it suits me, and you. i never slept until near six this morning. we saw Mr Ralwin[?] and Mr Broaks[?], both in deep mourning[?]. Send my cloak my local Mrs Phillips, the name of our new friend, and i were looking about all the evening, for a face, a countenance, as amiable, and as intelligent as yours, but our search was useless, not one, individual in the room, would bear the least comparison. Oh! you know not how much i value you, how happy am i, in having you for a companion, and friend! Dear, amiable, and as beautiful, as amiable, Richard, accept, the pure and artless love, and adoration of you Isis ['tis?] a love as servant, as pure, and as lasting as both! </p>
